name: Queen of Ancient Egypt - Cleopatra
description:
women around the world - (Cleopatra) Queen of Ancient Egypt

Cleopatra herself is described as the Queen of Ancient Egypt who has a super beautiful face. Her beauty was even able to melt Mark Anthony and Julius Caesar. Even so, Cleopatra was not just beautiful. More than that, there are many interesting things that Cleopatra has.

Many people know Cleopatra as the last Queen of the Ancient Egyptian Empire. But you may not know, if Cleopatra was not actually a native of Egypt. Cleopatra was born in Egypt with the name Cleopatra VII Philopator.
While he was born in Egypt, his family is of Greek Macedonian origin. He is a descendant of Ptolemy I Soter, a general of Alexander the Great. When Alexander the Great finally died in 323 BC, Ptolemy I Soter took his reign over Egypt.
Just like most nobles in the past, Cleopatra's family also often did inter-family marriages to keep their descendants with royal blood. The same thing happened to Cleopatra, she married at a young age with her two older brothers, namely Ptolemy XIII and Ptolemy XIV.
